<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Patch>

  <!-- Issue #54: under Combat Extended, make a player mechanoid's CE carry weight equal its CarryingCapacity (the
       mech's UI carry stat) so it hauls per its carrying capacity instead of CE's body-size default (~42 for any
       0.7-body mech), and so CE's per-pickup fit check + move-speed encumbrance are tuned to that capacity rather
       than fighting it. See HaulersDream.StatPart_MechCarryWeightCE — it only affects player mechs; every other
       pawn keeps CE's own CarryWeight.

       Gated by PatchOperationConditional on the CarryWeight StatDef existing, which is true only when Combat
       Extended (any variant) is loaded — so this is a no-op (no patch error) without CE, regardless of CE's mod
       display name. The non-CE case is handled in code by HaulersDream.CarryCapacity. -->
  <Operation Class="PatchOperationConditional">
    <xpath>/Defs/StatDef[defName="CarryWeight"]/parts</xpath>
    <match Class="PatchOperationAdd">
      <xpath>/Defs/StatDef[defName="CarryWeight"]/parts</xpath>
      <value>
        <li Class="HaulersDream.StatPart_MechCarryWeightCE" />
      </value>
    </match>
  </Operation>

</Patch>
